SIMPLE: novitiate
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Novitiate
<hw>No*vi"ti*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>novitiatus</ets>: cf. F. <ets>noviciat</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The state of being a novice; time of initiation or
instruction in rudiments.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <specif>Hence:</specif> <def>The time of probation in a
religious house before taking the vows.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>One who is going through a novitiate, or period of
probation; a novice.</def> <rj><au>Addison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>The place where novices live or are trained.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Novitious</ent>⟦br⟧
